Installing multiple free apps/ebooks to a single device tag in one go
2015-05-14 18:21
Apps/eBooks Distribution and Management
<p><span style="line-height: 1.4em;">With Cellabus, you have the flexibility of installing multiple apps on all devices with&nbsp;the same device tag. This is particularly useful when setting up a new batch of devices making it super fast to install the right apps.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="line-height: 1.4em;">Before installing apps, ensure that you have enough licenses, or "purchase" additional ones from Apple's VPP Store. &nbsp;Due to a change in Apple's policies, pushing free apps without purchasing and assigning licenses first, results in an iTunes password prompt on iPads. Licenses for apps assigned using the following steps are automatically assigned by Cellabus &nbsp;</span></p><ol style="font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal;"><li>Go the "tags" page and click on the tag that you want to install apps/ebooks&nbsp;on.</li><li>For content already added to the Cellabus catalog, within the "Install content" table on the right, click on the appropriate&nbsp;tab for the type of content (apps/ebooks/files) you want to install</li><li>To install a particular&nbsp;content, click on the "Install" button next to it.</li><li><span style="font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: 19.6000003814697px;">This can be done for as many apps/ebooks/files without having to leave the page.&nbsp;</span></li></ol><p style="font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: 19.6000003814697px;">&nbsp;</p><p><img src="/static/articles/tagapp.png" alt=""></p><p><br></p><div></div>
